    clinicalSigns: ["Delayed relaxation of deep tendon reflexes (hung-up reflexes)", "Bradycardia", "Cool, dry, pale skin", "Periorbital and peripheral edema (non-pitting)", "Goiter (Hashimoto) or absent (post-surgical/RAI)", "Coarse, brittle hair", "Macroglossia (enlarged tongue)", "Hoarse voice"],
    diagnosticCriteria: 'Elevated TSH (>4.5 mIU/L) with low free T4 confirms primary hypothyroidism. Anti-TPO antibodies positive in Hashimoto thyroiditis. Subclinical: elevated TSH with normal free T4. Screening recommended for at-risk populations.',
