    patientEducation: ["Hypothyroidism is treated with daily thyroid hormone replacement - this is NOT a cure but replaces what your body is missing", "Take levothyroxine on an empty stomach with water, wait 30-60 minutes before eating", "Do NOT take with calcium, iron, antacids, or fiber supplements (separate by 4 hours)", "You will need lifelong treatment with regular blood tests to monitor your dose", "Notify your doctor if you become pregnant (dose will need to increase)", "Do not stop or change your dose without consulting your doctor"],
