    prognosis: 'Varies widely by cancer type, stage at diagnosis, and treatment response. 5-year survival ranges from >90% (testicular, thyroid, melanoma in situ, breast local) to <5% (pancreatic, mesothelioma). Early detection dramatically improves outcomes.',
    prevention: ["Tobacco avoidance and smoking cessation", "Healthy weight, diet, and physical activity", "Limit alcohol consumption", "Sun protection and avoid tanning beds", "Vaccination (HPV, HBV)", "Cancer screening programs (mammogram, colonoscopy, Pap smear, low-dose CT for lung)", "Chemoprevention in high-risk groups"],
